    <header class="text-center mb-5">
      <h1>Streamlining Course Enrollment for Students</h1>
      <p class="lead">A UX case study focused on improving student usability in course registration.</p>
      <img src="https://plus.unsplash.com/premium_photo-1672252617505-b6149ea20fcf?fm=jpg&q=60&w=3000&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxzZWFyY2h8MXx8YWVzdGhldGljJTIwZmxvd2VyfGVufDB8fDB8fHww" alt="Project image" class="img-fluid rounded mt-3 shadow-sm">
    </header>

    <section class="mb-5">
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>Partnered with six peers to reimagine the UCI WebReg system with a modern, student-centered interface. Conducted usability testing, built wireframes and interactive prototypes in Figma, and designed features to simplify course search, scheduling, and registration.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-5">
      <h2>Problem</h2>
      <p>The existing WebReg system had a confusing interface, making it hard for students to search courses, plan schedules, and register efficiently.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-5">
      <h2>Process</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Conducted user interviews to understand pain points.</li>
        <li>Created wireframes and interactive prototypes in Figma.</li>
        <li>Tested usability with real students and iterated on feedback.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-5">
      <h2>Outcome</h2>
      <p>Designed an intuitive interface that reduced navigation friction and simplified course enrollment, improving student satisfaction and task completion speed.</p>
    </section>

